{
  "texts": [
    "The EHT data provide two relevant estimates of the total flux densities at different spatial scales.",
    "The first one is the total flux density of the arcsecond-scale radio core, constrained by the short intra-site baselines.",
    "The total flux density as measured by the ALMA-only interferometric observations was F tot ≈ 1.13 Jy A79, page 9 of 63",
    "The Event Horizon Telescope Collaboration: A&A, 681, A79 (2024) by averaging the values over four bands on April 21 and 22.",
    "The second one is the total compact flux density, F cpct ≤ F tot, which is the integrated flux density of the microarcsecond-scale structure constrained by inter-site baselines."
  ]
}